Calculating the standard deviation and selecting the top 1000 variable genes

exp_set <- as.data.frame(Exp_set)
nm1 <- colnames(exp_set)
library(matrixStats)
## 
## Attaching package: 'matrixStats'
## The following object is masked from 'package:dplyr':
## 
##     count
## The following objects are masked from 'package:Biobase':
## 
##     anyMissing, rowMedians
exp_dev <- exp_set %>%
  mutate(stdev=rowSds(as.matrix(.[nm1])))
#we will reorder the data descending
exp_dev <- exp_dev %>%
  arrange(desc(stdev))
#we will select the top 1000 gene based on their standard deviation
exp_dev <- exp_dev %>%
  slice(1:1000)
